# CODEOWNERS - Define code ownership for review requirements
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Each line is a file pattern followed by one or more owners.
# Order matters: later patterns take precedence over earlier ones.
# Owners can be @username, @org/team-name, or email@example.com

# =============================================================================
# Default Owners
# =============================================================================
# These owners will be requested for review when someone opens a PR
# that modifies code that doesn't match any later pattern.

*                       @your-username

# =============================================================================
# Directory-Specific Owners
# =============================================================================

# API / Backend
# /src/api/             @backend-team
# /internal/            @backend-team

# Frontend
# /src/frontend/        @frontend-team
# /src/components/      @frontend-team
# /src/pages/           @frontend-team

# Documentation
# /docs/                @docs-team
# *.md                  @docs-team

# =============================================================================
# Critical Files (Require Senior Review)
# =============================================================================

# GitHub configuration - impacts CI/CD and security
/.github/               @your-username
/.github/workflows/     @your-username

# Security-related files
/SECURITY.md            @your-username
/.pre-commit-config.yaml @your-username

# Configuration files
*.json                  @your-username
*.yaml                  @your-username
*.yml                   @your-username
*.toml                  @your-username

# =============================================================================
# Infrastructure
# =============================================================================

# Docker
# Dockerfile            @devops-team
# docker-compose*.yml   @devops-team

# Kubernetes
# /k8s/                 @devops-team
# /helm/                @devops-team

# Terraform
# /terraform/           @devops-team
# *.tf                  @devops-team

# =============================================================================
# Language-Specific
# =============================================================================

# Go
# go.mod                @backend-team
# go.sum                @backend-team

# Python
# requirements*.txt     @backend-team
# pyproject.toml        @backend-team
# setup.py              @backend-team

# Node.js
# package.json          @frontend-team
# package-lock.json     @frontend-team
# tsconfig.json         @frontend-team

# =============================================================================
# Notes
# =============================================================================
# - Replace @your-username with your GitHub username
# - Replace team names like @backend-team with actual GitHub teams
# - Uncomment relevant sections based on your project structure
# - Add team members as needed: @user1 @user2 @org/team-name
